    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-04T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-04T22:00:00-05:00" n="678"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1613: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-05T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 5, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 5—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 68, March 2, 5 p.m. British Minister has thus far received no instructions
                    regarding Boxer Indemnity. Italian Chargé d’Affaires informs me that at the
                    request of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_STV1">Soong</persName> he has asked
                    his Government to reconsider their position. I shall refrain from saying
                    anything to <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_STV1">Soong</persName> unless
                    pressed further or hear further from British.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
